&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 5 Nurse Adviser&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full time/Part time (Weekdays exc Bank Holidays)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic and highly motivated Band 5 nurse to join the Nurse Advisor Team in the Occupational Health Department, working across both sites at St James Hospital, Leeds and the Leeds General Infirmary.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience in Occupational Health is desirable but not essential, as training will be given to the right candidate. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are a registered nurse with an interest in workplace health, looking to start or develop your career in Occupational Health Nursing, and you have at least two years post-registration experience, then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a busy department and the Nurse Advisors are part of a multi-disciplinary team, providing a comprehensive SEQOHS accredited Occupational Health Service to a large NHS workforce, and to private clients including students. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We use electronic records and so the successful candidate will need to be comfortable working with IT systems.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We require a good team player who is able to work well within a multi-professional team but who is equally self- motivated and able to work autonomously.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information please contact Jeannie Patterson, Senior Nurse, or Ngozi Ibe / Theresa Odetoyinbo/ Helen Baldwin, Specialist Nurse Practitioners on 0113 206 5228. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Informal visits are welcomed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
